Sentencas: Direct utilization and internal reforming of gaseous fuels is investigated on symmetric architecture metal supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) with thin ceramic electrolyte and scaffold backbone layers, and low cost ferritic stainless steel supports on both sides.
Titulo: Direct utilization of gaseous fuels in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Infiltrated Pr-oxide and Ni/samarium-doped ceria catalysts are added to the cathode and anode electrodes, respectively.
Titulo: Direct utilization of gaseous fuels in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Initial performance and durability is evaluated for MSSOFCs operating with natural gas, propane, ammonia, and dimethyl ether at 700 degrees C. Cells for natural gas and propane utilize a novel high entropy alloy (HEA) catalyst for internal reforming with performance and degradation rates similar to H-2 (0.5 W cm(-2) and similar to 12%/ 100 h).
Titulo: Direct utilization of gaseous fuels in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Initial testing with sulfur shows reversible degradation for levels found in natural gas and irreversible degradation for higher levels found in commercial propane.
Titulo: Direct utilization of gaseous fuels in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Overall, MS-SOFCs show successful fuel flexibility.
Titulo: Direct utilization of gaseous fuels in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells
